an conception of time, with each day of the year celebrating the death of a saint. From Roman antiquity to medieval England, through the Protestant Reformation and up to the present, Cult of the Dead tells the fascinating story of how the world’s most widespread religion is steeped in the memory of martyrs.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aChristian martyrsxCultxHistory. 0aChristian saintsxCultxHistory. 0aChurch historyyPrimitive and early church, ca. 30-600. 0aDeathxReligious aspectsxHistory. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / History.2bisacsh  abiblical.  acatholic.  acatholicism.  achrist.  achristianity.  afigures.  ahalloween.  aholiness.  ajesus.  ajude.  alegends.  amartyrs.  amary.  amedieval england.  amoses.  amythology.  areligion.  areligious studies.  aroman.  asaints.  athe bible.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2022 Englishz978311099291508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2022z9783110992878oZDB-23-DGD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z97831107664930 cprintz978052034516440uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520975712?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520975712423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520975712/original  a978-3-11-076649-3  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099291-5  EBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  a